0.1 Summary

The Search Console Api has many data about customers has many searchs for own page. For example, one can look at how weekly, day or monthly clicks have been decreasing in many landing pages of the site, while impresion has risen. In this report, Overview of keywords in a dummy site is analysed, and a comparison between 2021-Jan-09 and 2021-02-05 is made. All analysed countries have seen a decrease in weekly working hours since 1996 some more than others.

Finding proportions and probabilities to approach the SEM strategies

key_1_total <- sum(na.exclude(count(searchs_separate,vars = key_1))$n)
key_2_total <- sum(na.exclude(count(searchs_separate,key_2))$n)
key_3_total <- sum(na.exclude(count(searchs_separate,key_3))$n)
total_consultas <- searchs_separate %>% count()
probabilidad_1w <- key_1_total/total_consultas
probabilida_2w <-round(x = key_2_total/total_consultas, digits = 2)
probabilida_3w <- round( x = key_3_total/total_consultas, digits = 2)

0.3.5 Text Mining Consultas 3 palabras

# Make tokenizer function 
tokenzier <- function(x) {
  NGramTokenizer(x, Weka_control(min = 3, max = 3))
 }
 
clean_corpus <- function(corpus) {
  # Remove punctuation
  corpus <- tm_map(corpus, removePunctuation)
  # Transform to lower case
"corpus <- tm_map(corpus, content_transform(tolower))"
  # Add more stopwords
  corpus <- tm_map(corpus, removeWords, words = c(stopwords("es"), "att", "para","joomshaper"))
  # Strip whitespace
  corpus <- tm_map(corpus,stripWhitespace)
  corpus <- tm_map(corpus,removePunctuation)
  return(corpus)
}
consultas_3 <- searchs_separate %>% filter(!is.na(key_3)) %>% unite("consulta",c(key_1:key_3),sep = " ", na.rm = TRUE, remove = TRUE)

consultas_corpus <- VectorSource(consultas_3$consulta)

# Make a volatile corpus from coffee_corpus
consultas_corpus_2 <- Corpus(consultas_corpus)

corpus_consultas_clean <- clean_corpus(consultas_corpus_2)
# Create unigram_dtm
unigram_dtm <- DocumentTermMatrix(corpus_consultas_clean)

# Create bigram_dtm
'trigram_dtm <- TermDocumentMatrix(
  corpus_consultas_clean,
  control = list(tokenize = tokenzier)
)'
## [1] "trigram_dtm <- TermDocumentMatrix(\n  corpus_consultas_clean,\n  control = list(tokenize = tokenzier)\n)"
consultas_matrix <- as.matrix(unigram_dtm)

# Print the dimensions of coffee_m

frecuencia_consultas <- colSums(consultas_matrix)
frecuencia_consultas <- frecuencia_consultas %>% sort(decreasing = TRUE)

wordcloud(corpus_consultas_clean, max.words = 50,

Going further there are associations

# Create associations
associations <- findAssocs(unigram_dtm, c("audifonos","diademas","cable","cargador","accesorios","iphone"), 0.05)
# Create associations_df
associations_df <- list_vect2df(associations,col1 = 'word_1' ,col2 = "word_2", col3 = "score")
associations_df <- associations_df %>% arrange(desc(score))

# Plot the associations_df values
ggplot(associations_df, aes(score, word_1, label = word_2)) + 
  geom_point(size = 3) + geom_text(aes(label = word_2),vjust = 3,check_overlap = TRUE) +
  theme_gdocs() + labs(x = "Word",y = "Score",title = "Asociaciones de Palabras")
